@page "/"

<PageTitle>GoodHamburguer</PageTitle>

<section class="hero hero-grid">
    <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Operations Hub</p>
        <h1>Run the kitchen with a cleaner command surface.</h1>
        <p>
            Monitor the menu, compose new orders, inspect live tickets, and keep the GoodHamburguer flow moving from a single premium control layer.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/dashboard/orders">Open orders board</a>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-primary" href="/menu">Browse product menu</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="hero-note">
        <span class="pill">Service ready</span>
        <strong>Menu, creation flow, details, and dashboard are linked to the live API.</strong>
        <p>
            The homepage now acts as an entry dashboard instead of a scaffold placeholder, matching the same industrial dark language used across the operational routes.
        </p>
    </aside>

    <div class="metric-grid">
        <article class="metric-card">
            <span>Frontend</span>
            <strong>Blazor Server</strong>
        </article>
        <article class="metric-card">
            <span>API</span>
            <strong>v1 Connected</strong>
        </article>
        <article class="metric-card">
            <span>Operations</span>
            <strong>Menu to Orders</strong>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>
